"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The heatmap function in seaborn expects a 2D dataset that can be coerced into an ndarray. The 'tips' DataFrame contains categorical columns that cannot be directly used to create a heatmap. The heatmap should be called with a 2D array or a DataFrame that contains numerical values only.\",\n  \"patch\": \"5c5\\n< g = sns.heatmap(tips, square=True, cbar_kws={'fraction': 0.01}, cmap='OrRd', linewidth=1)\\n---\\n> g = sns.heatmap(tips.pivot_table(values='tip', index='day', columns='sex'), square=True, cbar_kws={'fraction': 0.01}, cmap='OrRd', linewidth=1)\"\n}"